These last few days I really feel like I’ve been walking on a cloud … I was a presenter at the @blacktattooexperience conference and I met and spent some real genuine time with the first known black tattooer Jacci Gresham @aartaccenttat2 ! I was even given the opportunity to present an award to her alongside one of my best friends @kandacelayne !!! I was asked at the conference what has been one of the biggest highlights of my career and of course I said opening my studio , but I honestly think my answer has changed. This right here is the biggest highlight ! Being able to give Jacci her flowers in real time is something il never forget and never get over! If she had not followed her dreams and stayed down through all the years of trials and hardships none of us would even have known that tattooing was something we could make a career . We are all here because of this one black woman and that’s so phenomenal to me! Thank you @swiss.premium for walking in your purpose and putting this all together! My heart is so Full 🖤🖤🖤 In the words of @amanitreniner  BEING BLACK IS A FLEX! I love us so much 🥹❤️🫶🏾

Let me start by saying, I only do cover-ups on a case by case basis. Keny came to me previously for one of my flash days. When she showed me her original tattoo, I honestly had no clue how we were gonna pull this off!  Every other artist had turned her down but I decided to take on the challenge just bc I loved Keny’s energy so much! She gave me complete creative control & let me do my thing! In 3 sessions we created something so beautiful for her to wear and be proud of!  I love the way this turned out! & thank you Keny for trusting me🫶🏾

 ✨ My books are open for the end of May & June! Link in bio ✨

If you’ve ever spoken to me about where I’m from or my family I’m pretty sure I’ve mentioned my auntie @debrakillings ! She’s a legend here in Atl in the music industry , a beast on the bass and just a all around talented and good woman ! If you’ve ever listened to TLC Outkast Goodie Mob Monica or Toni Braxton you’ve heard my aunties basslines or vocals! And I’m lucky enough to be named after her 🥰 She’s been asking me to paint one of her bass for years and I honestly was just too scared to do it! Idk what it was but this year I finally got out of my own way and just did it! It took my almost 5 months but I absolutely love how it turned out ! I even changed out the pick guard to add the perfect final touch!!! If you know me you know Il go to the end of the world for my family especially for my Auntie Debra ! Here’s the months of hard work all wrapped up into a minute or so ! 💕💕💕 I don’t know if il ever do another one but I really love this and will always love my auntie for pushing me out my comfort zone and asking me to do this for her 😘 

#blackgirlmagic #bassplayer #bassguitar #femalebassplayer #legendary #ATL

Transparency moment : 
Being a business owner is hard. Becoming a mother for the first time is even harder. Trying to combine the two feels like utter chaos most days.  I'm almost 11 months postpartum and I still feel like I'm in a haze. My mind is so slippery but I'm doing my best and I’m getting better every single day. I say all this to say, give people grace. Hell, give me grace. If I don't answer your email immediately please give me 24-72 hours before you resend it. If I miss your consultation and email you to reschedule just respond and let me know if you're still interested or not.  I'm human ya’ll , I'm not a computer. I don't have a huge team backing me. I'm just a small business owner and a new mom trying to get a grip on this new life. That’s all 🤷🏾‍♀️ & huge S/o to  @miked.shotme for capturing these photos of me. They so moody and beautiful ! I just love them and you bro 💚💓💚 

#sis #justamomtryingtomakeit #workinmoms #femalebusinessowner

Everything I’ve been wanting is manifesting in my life ! I’ve been talking about teaching an Art Therapy class for so long and  thanks to @toyota  Music Academy @iam_mali  @earthgirlatl & @stonewoodranchestates it finally happened!!! I’m so grateful for Mali for opening her space to us ! I’m also so grateful I got the opportunity to share this platform with one of my sisters @emotionalexchange ! We’ve been friends for so long our chemistry is just unmatched! We spoke about color theory , color psychology, & what color can do for your soul. We had thought provoking convos about Confidence Compassion & Community. We were able to give away a full paintbrush set , sticker packs, and journals to everyone who participated. I hope it helps to ignite the artist in each and every one of you ! I can’t wait to do more classes like this and share my knowledge and gifts with the world ✨ 

#snaxink #sis #earthgirl #blackgirlmagic #blackartmatters #art #artteacher #arttherapy

I made these loving owls for my childhood friend @msstempossible as a memorial tribute to her husband back in August. Not too long after we made this tattoo, she transitioned as well.🕊️ Her birthday was this Tuesday so I figured this is the perfect time to share this beautiful tattoo I made for her 🥹 Honestly,I had a really hard time processing & even posting this one. I find peace knowing that you and your hubby are together again 🧡I’m sure y’all are up there snuggled up just like these owls 🫶🏾 Happy birthday Erika, you are an inspiration to so many young black female engineers . I’m glad you got your flowers and your statue while you were still here to see it all.💕 ✨🕊️✨💕
